.TH "ssam_notifier_register" 9 "ssam_notifier_register" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ssam_notifier_register \- Register an event notifier.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" ssam_notifier_register
.BI "(struct ssam_controller *ctrl "  ","
.BI "struct ssam_event_notifier *n "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ctrl" 12
The controller to register the notifier on.
.IP "n" 12
The event notifier to register.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Register an event notifier and increment the usage counter of the
associated SAM event. If the event was previously not enabled, it will be
enabled during this call.
.SH "RETURN"
Returns zero on success, -ENOSPC if there have already been
INT_MAX notifiers for the event ID/type associated with the notifier block
registered, -ENOMEM if the corresponding event entry could not be
allocated. If this is the first time that a notifier block is registered
for the specific associated event, returns the status of the event-enable
EC-command.
